                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.48 FRP/10–1747: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-10-17T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 17, 1947—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1275. <hi rend="smallcaps">Rap</hi> 176. Dept agrees with assumptions re relief
                    agreement set forth in Shanghai’s 2420 Oct 14 (<hi rend="smallcaps">Par</hi>
                    32). Sent Nanking as Depts 1275 repeated to Shanghai as Depts 1778. Dept does
                    not desire approve text of proposed answer to request for interpretation
                    provided the sentences set forth in Deptel 1247 Oct 8 are included and no other
                    matters of policy are added.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
